ALgorithm

Step 1: Start.
Step 2: Import the pandas and matplotlib.pyplot libraries.
Step 3: Initialize a dictionary containing a list of 10 student names and a corresponding list of their total marks.
Step 4: Convert this dictionary into a Pandas DataFrame to organize the data into a tabular format.
Step 5: Create a new plot figure and set its dimensions to 10x6 inches.
Step 6: Generate a Bar Chart using the student names from the DataFrame for the X-axis and their total marks for the Y-axis.
Step 7: Set the bar color to sky blue and the edge color to black.
Step 8: Add a title to the chart and label both the X-axis and the Y-axis.
Step 9: Rotate the X-axis tick labels (the student names) by 45 degrees so they do not overlap each other.
Step 10: Apply the tight_layout() function to adjust the spacing and prevent the labels from getting cut off.
Step 11: Display the final graphical chart to the screen using the show() function.
Step 12: Stop.
